	<short_description>
		avahi (service discovery aka zeroconf)
	</short_description>
	<description>
		Avahi is an Implementation the DNS Service Discovery and Multicast DNS
 specifications
 for Zeroconf Computing. It uses D-BUS for communication between user
 applications
 and a system daemon. The daemon is used to coordinate application efforts in
 caching
 replies, necessary to minimize the traffic imposed on networks. This kind of 
 technology is already found in Apple MacOS X (branded Rendezvous Bonjour and 
 sometimes Zeroconf) and is very convenient.
	</description>
